.TH "usb4_switch_drom_read" 9 "usb4_switch_drom_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb4_switch_drom_read \- Read arbitrary bytes from USB4 router DROM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb4_switch_drom_read
.BI "(struct tb_switch *sw "  ","
.BI "unsigned int address "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sw" 12
USB4 router
.IP "address" 12
Byte address inside DROM to start reading
.IP "buf" 12
Buffer where the DROM content is stored
.IP "size" 12
Number of bytes to read from DROM
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Uses USB4 router operations to read router DROM. For devices this
should always work but for hosts it may return -EOPNOTSUPP in which
case the host router does not have DROM.
